value.value: 胚換気の増加

increase in the respiratory minute volume, or the total volume of gas per minute inspired or expired expressed in liters per minute; refers to the exchange of air between the total respiratory space and the environment

definition.value: Do not confuse with pulmonary ventilation rate (aka respiratory rate). Pulmonary ventilation is the volume of air per minute; pulmonary ventilation rate is the number of breaths per minute.

value.value: 胚換気の減少

reduction in the respiratory minute volume, or the total volume of gas per minute inspired or expired expressed in liters per minute; refers to the exchange of air between the total respiratory space and the environment

definition.value: Do not confuse with pulmonary ventilation rate (aka respiratory rate). Pulmonary ventilation is the volume of air per minute; pulmonary ventilation rate is the number of breaths per minute.

label.value: increased susceptibility to type I hypersensitivity reaction

value.value: Ⅰ型過敏症反応に対する感受性上昇

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: increased susceptibility to type I hypersensitivity reaction

value.value: greater likelihood of developing a response manifested by localized or generalized reaction that occurs immediately (minutes) after exposure to an antigen to which the person/animal was previously sensitized; it is IgE-mediated, and mast cell activation and degranulation are hallmarks

definition.value: Examples of this type of hypersensitivity include hay fever, asthma, and anaphylaxis.

label.value: decreased susceptibility to type I hypersensitivity reaction

value.value: Ⅰ型過敏症反応に対する感受性低下

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: decreased susceptibility to type I hypersensitivity reaction

value.value: less likelihood or resistance to developing a response manifested by localized or generalized reaction that occurs immediately (minutes) after exposure to an antigen to which the person/animal was previously sensitized; it is IgE-mediated, and mast cell activation and degranulation are hallmarks

definition.value: Examples of this type of hypersensitivity include hay fever, asthma, and anaphylaxis.

value.value: 心室筋の収縮性減少

心筋の収縮性増加

greater than the normal ability of the heart muscle to shorten or to develop increased tension, often measured by dP/dT max, fractional shortening (FS), velocity of circumferential fiber shortening (Vcfc), peak of aortic outflow velocity (PAV), and ventricular ejection fraction volume
心室筋の収縮性増加
greater than the normal ability of the heart ventricle muscle to shorten or to develop increased tension, often measured by ventricular ejection fraction volume

血管形成の減少

ニューロンの肥大

心臓間質繊維症
formation of fibrous tissue within the interstices of the heart as a result of repair or a reactive process
抗利尿ホルモンの血中濃度異常

label.value: decreased susceptibility to type II hypersensitivity reaction

value.value: Ⅱ型過敏症反応に対する感受性低下

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: decreased susceptibility to type II hypersensitivity reaction

value.value: less likelihood of or resistance to developing a response caused by an Ag-Ab reaction; antibodies are directly or indirectly cytotoxic to antigens on cell surfaces or in connective tissues; most often involves IgG and IgM; complement activation is usually involved

definition.value: Examples of this include: autoimmune diseases: autoimmune hemolytic anemias, antibody-dependent cellular cytotoxicity (ADCC), Goodpasture disease, myasthenia gravis, Graves disease, pemphigus, and pemphigoid.

label.value: increased susceptibility to type II hypersensitivity reaction

value.value: Ⅱ型過敏症反応に対する感受性上昇

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: increased susceptibility to type II hypersensitivity reaction

value.value: greater likelihood or resistance to developing a response caused by an Ag-Ab reaction; antibodies are directly or indirectly cytotoxic to antigens on cell surfaces or in connective tissues; most often involves IgG and IgM; complement activation is usually involved

definition.value: Examples of this include: autoimmune diseases: autoimmune hemolytic anemias, antibody-dependent cellular cytotoxicity (ADCC), Goodpasture disease, myasthenia gravis, Graves disease, pemphigus, and pemphigoid.

label.value: decreased susceptibility to type III hypersensitivity reaction

value.value: Ⅲ型過敏症反応に対する感受性低下

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: decreased susceptibility to type III hypersensitivity reaction

value.value: less likelihood of or resistance to developing tissue injury mediated by immune complexes; generally involves immune complexes formed in the blood via Abs encountering circulating Ag; Ag-Ab complexes then deposit in tissues (especially blood vessels and glomeruli), induce complement activation, and result in tissue injury

definition.value: Examples of this include: Autoimmune diseases: systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE), rheumatoid arthritis, Sjogren syndrome, scleroderma, and glomerulonephritis.

label.value: increased susceptibility to type III hypersensitivity reaction

value.value: Ⅲ型過敏症反応に対する感受性上昇

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: increased susceptibility to type III hypersensitivity reaction

value.value: greater likelihood of developing tissue injury mediated by immune complexes; generally involves immune complexes formed in the blood via antibodies encountering circulating antigen; Ag-Ab complexes then deposit in tissues (especially blood vessels and glomeruli), induce complement activation, and result in tissue injury

definition.value: Examples of this include: Autoimmune diseases: systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE), rheumatoid arthritis, Sjogren syndrome, scleroderma, and glomerulonephritis.

label.value: decreased susceptibility to type IV hypersensitivity reaction

value.value: Ⅳ型過敏症反応に対する感受性低下

https://w3id.org/babelon/source_value.value: decreased susceptibility to type IV hypersensitivity reaction

value.value: less likelihood of or resistance to developing an antigen-elicited cellular immune reaction that results in tissue damage, but does not require Ab participation; the response is seen at the area of contact

definition.value: Examples of this include: granulomatous diseases: tuberculosis, and sarcoidosis contact dermatitis: elicited by poison ivy, detergents, clothing, etc.

value.value: 尿中カリウム濃度低下
less than the normal amount of potassium in the urine
尿中カリウム濃度上昇
greater than normal amount of potassium in the urine
筋肉の収縮性異常
aberrant ability of a muscle to shorten or to develop increased tension
細胞の生理異常
any functional anomaly of the vital processes of the cell
髄膜の形態異常
any structural anomaly in any of the membranes covering the spinal cord and brain, including the dura mater (external), arachnoid (middle), and pia mater (internal)
血漿のアニオンギャップ異常

measurement of the interval between the sum of routinely measured cations minus the sum of the routinely measured anions in the blood; the anion gap = (Na+ + K+) - (Cl- + HCO3-) where Na- is sodium, K+ is potassium, Cl- is chloride, and HCO3- is bicarbonate
血漿のアニオンギャップ増加

greater than the normal interval between the sum of routinely measured cations minus the sum of the routinely measured anions in the blood; the anion gap = (Na+ + K+) - (Cl- + HCO3-) where Na- is sodium, K+ is potassium, Cl- is chloride, and HCO3- is bicarbonate; high anion gap is indicative of metabolic acidosis
血漿のアニオンギャップ減少

less than the normal interval between the sum of routinely measured cations minus the sum of the routinely measured anions in the blood; the anion gap = (Na+ + K+) - (Cl- + HCO3-) where Na- is sodium, K+ is potassium, Cl- is chloride, and HCO3- is bicarbonate; low anion gap is relatively rare but may occur from the presence of abnormal positively charged proteins, as in multiple myeloma
カリウム血中濃度上昇

greater than the normal concentration in the blood of this alkaline metallic element, the most abundant intracellular ion; anomalies in the extracellular (circulating) concentration have important implications for the function of excitable tissues, such as nerve and muscle
カリウム血中濃度低下

less than the normal concentration in the blood of this alkaline metallic element, the most abundant intracellular ion; anomalies in the extracellular (circulating) concentration have important implications for the function of excitable tissues, such as nerve and muscle
肺重量の異常
anomaly in the average weight of the lung
